cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
title: "Teaching Large Language Models how to Code"
abstract: >
  A multi-stage pipeline that uses AutoGen multi-agent prompt engineering,
  GRPO reinforcement learning, DSPy automated prompt optimisation, and
  SpaCy MCP tools to teach large language models structured information
  extraction (subject-verb relationship detection) from social-media texts.
authors:
  - family-names: Loertscher
    given-names: Pierre
    affiliation: "University of Chicago, Crown Family School / MACSS Program"
date-released: "2026-03-13"
url: "https://github.com/ploertscher/ai_agents_project"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - large language models
  - multi-agent systems
  - prompt engineering
  - reinforcement learning from human feedback
  - DSPy
  - AutoGen
  - information extraction
  - social media analysis
